issue.title: Implemented Vue front end
issue.body:
A mostly complete Vue.js framework implementation of what we currently have.

The point of this fat PR:
- Scalability of the front-end
- Maintainability
- Separation of concerns between back-end and front-end

Missing Features:
- Sign up error and success indicators, log in error indicators (You can still sign up and log in just fine!). Working on it.
- Instagram Flow (You can still view its settings just fine if you process it through the back-end server)

Currently somewhat broken:
- The coloring of optimal settings. Looking into it.
- Twitter oauth redirects to the back-end url rather than the front-end url.

TODO:
- Revamp the settings page into something with a little pizzazz. 
- Add global back-end url for easier API calls

To test:
Start both the back-end and front-end servers (through node app/src and npm run serve in their respective folders). You'll need multiple command windows for this -- this can be done through a new IDE window or console window.

Explore the shiny front-end with the appropriate url!
